tion-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%20is%20bolstering%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20newly%20released%20security%20report%2C%20Meta%20identified%20Russia%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bnumber%20one%20source%26quot%3B%20of%20global%20coordinated%20inauthentic%20behavior%20(or%20CIB)%20efforts.%20The%20nation%20has%20at%20least%2039%20%26quot%3Bcovert%20influence%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20Meta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20influence%20operations%20used%20generative%20AI%20to%20create%20personas%20for%20fake%20journalists%20and%20publish%20stories%20on%20fictitious%20news%20sites%20with%20distorted%20information%20from%20authentic%20articles%2C%20Meta%20said%20in%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20past%20Russian%20efforts%20to%20influence%20US%20politics%20relied%20on%20hot-button%20social%20and%20cultural%20issues%20in%20a%20given%20country%20to%20gain%20traction%2C%20the%20current%20%26quot%3Bdeceptive%20campaign%26quot%3B%20is%20mostly%20focused%20on%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20for%20which%20Russian%20operators%20are%20trying%20to%20rally%20support%2C%20the%20Meta%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20had%20a%20frosty%20relationship%20with%20Meta%20since%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022.%20Facebook%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-pulls-ads-russia-blocks-all-russian-advertisers-globally-ukraine-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epulled%20all%20advertising%20in%20Russia%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20blocked%20Russian%20ads%20shortly%20after%20the%20invasion.%20Months%20later%2C%20Russia%20categorized%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-adds-meta-list-extremist-terrorist-groups-facebook-zuckerberg-report-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20as%20an%20extremist%20and%20terrorist%3C%2Fa%3E%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetween%20now%20and%20the%20US%20elections%20in%20November