%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sportsbookreview.com%2Fnews%2Fus-betting-revenue-tracker%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESports%20Book%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20said%20US%20households%20bet%20an%20average%20of%20%241%2C100%20per%20year%2C%20or%20%24280%20a%20quarter%20%E2%80%94%20a%20number%20that's%20continued%20to%20grow%20by%20%2425%20per%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20researchers%20found%20that%20net%20investments%20typically%20fell%20nearly%2014%25%20in%20the%20two%20to%20three%20years%20after%20a%20legalization%20occurred%20in%20a%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20study%20noted%20that%20financially%20constrained%20households%20tend%20to%20contribute%20a%20larger%20chunk%20of%20their%20income%20toward%20sports%20gambling%2C%20and%20are%20therefore%20hit%20harder%20by%20the%20negative%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20households%2C%20already%20in%20relatively%20bad%20financial%20shape%2C%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20divert%20funds%20from%20their%20investment%20portfolios%20to%20betting%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BGiven%20that%20sports%20betting%20has%20a%20negative%20expected%20value%2C%20this%20finding%20underscores%20the%20potential%20for%20sports%20betting%20legalization%20to%20exacerbate%20financial%20vulnerability%20and%20hardship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsports-betting-debt-bankruptcy-gambling-young-men-research-addiction-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparate%20recent%20working%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20reached%20a%20similar%20conclusion%2C%20outlining%20how%20credit%20has%20been%20damaged%20in%20areas%20where%20sports%20gambling%20is%20legal.%20In%20these%20areas%2C%20credit%20scores%20have%20dipped%201%25%2C%20while%20debt%20collection%20and%20bankruptcies%20have%20jumped%208%25%20and%2028%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20never%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20Michelle%20Malkin%2C%20the%20director%20of%20East%20Carolina%20University's%20Gambling%20Research%20%26amp%3B%20Policy%20Initiative%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20keep%20on%20gambling.%20So%20it's%20this%20cyclical%20thought%20pattern%20of%2C%20'I%20can%20fix%20my%20problems%20by%20keeping%20gambling%20and%20getting%20that%20next%20win.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-investing-impact-legal-sport-betting-gambling-study-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723898462000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bf81865da406397bf69c8c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-investing-impact-legal-sport-betting-gambling-study-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Household%20investments%20are%20reduced%20by%20roughly%20%242%20for%20ever%20dollar%20wagered%2C%20the%20researchers%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22fdemott%40insider.com%20(Filip%20De%20Mott)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-investing-impact-legal-sport-betting-gambling-study-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%2058%25%20of%20blue-collar%20jobs%20pay%20less%20than%20Rs%2020%2C000%20per%20month%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723898410000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-06%2F20%2Fthumb%2Ffeaturecrop%2F400X400%2F1718854698-5418.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fover-58-of-blue-collar-jobs-pay-less-than-rs-20-000-per-month-report-124081700536_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20addition%2C%20the%20report%20revealed%20that%20about%2029.34%20per%