3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20the%20risks%20to%20the%20outlook%20for%20India%20-%20one%20of%20the%20downside%20risks%20is%20climate%20related.%20We%20are%20seeing%20that%20in%20terms%20of%20volatility%20in%20rainfall%2C%20predicting%20that%20rainfall%20and%20implications%20for%20harvest%20and%20rural%20incomes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20economist%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20temperature%20rise%20in%20Asia%20has%20been%20higher%20than%20the%20world%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20looked%20at%20Asia%20as%20a%20region%20as%20a%20whole%20and%20you%20see%20the%20increase%20in%20temperatures%20that%20you%20see%20in%20Asia%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20world%20average.%20Specifically%20for%20India%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%201950%20to%202018%2C%20temperatures%20have%20gone%20up%20by%20half%20a%20degree%20centigrade%20and%20that%20has%20real%20consequences%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Ms%20Gopinath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20highlighted%20how%20global%20climate%20disasters%20could%20pose%20a%20bigger%20financial%20challenge%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20costs%20of%20the%20climate%20disasters%20(globally)%20that%20we%20have%20seen%20starting%20from%201980%20onwards%20has%20been%20about%20half%20a%20percentage%20point%20of%20GDP%20per%20year%20and%20our%20expectation%20is%20that%20over%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20that%20cost%20will%20be%20about%200.3%20percentage%20points.%20So%2C%20this%20is%20a%20very%20serious%20threat%20that%20the%20world%20faces%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ms%20Gopinath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20action%20is%20needed%20to%20tackle%20climate%20change%2C%20including%20from%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20the%20IMF%20economist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20a%20potential%20solution%2C%20she%20said%20a%20package%20subsidising%20renewable%20energy%20and%20with%20a%20carbon%20pricing%20scheme%20can%20deliver%20a%20clean-energy%20transition.%20Trillions%20of%20dollars%20needed%20for%20the%20world%20to%20make%20a%20clean-energy%20transition%2C%20she%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20much%20as%2090%25%20of%20clean-energy%20transition%20funding%20has%20to%20come%20from%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Lower%20Employment%20Growth'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20India%2C%20she%20said%20the%20country%20has%20done%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20well%26quot%3B%20in%20terms%20of%20headline%20growth%20and%20pointed%20out%20it%20is%20the%20fastest%20growing%20major%20economy%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20noted%20that%20employment%20growth%20has%20been%20lower%20than%202%25%20in%20India.%20%26quot%3BIndia's%20growth%20has%20been%20capital%20intensive%2C%20but%20hiring%20workers%20has%20been%20much%20less.%20India%20needs%20more%20investment%20in%20human%20capital%20and%20skilling%20workers.%20Jobs%20between%2060-148%20million%20need%20to%20be%20created%20between%20now%20and%202030%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20elaborated%20on%20the%20challenges%20and%20opportunities%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20its%20implication%20in%20the%20context%20of%20Indian%20job%20market.%20%26quot%3BGenerative%20AI%20is%20making%20services%20more%20automated%20and%2024%25%20of%20India's%20labour%20force%20is%20exposed%20to%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723888980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F9u98rnc_gita-gopinath-ndtv_625x300_17_August_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fgita-gopinath-to-ndtv-climate-change-a-downside-risk-to-indian-economy-6356949%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gita%20Gopinath%20of%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20has%20flagged%20a%20downside%20risk%20to%20the%20Indian%20economic%20outlook%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engag